## DTO Shapes

### Simulate Request (FE → BE): `UnitaryRequestDTO`
```typescript
{
  gates: string[] | Array<{name: string, theta: number}>,  // gate names or parameterized gates
  qubit_order: string[],       // e.g. ["C0_T1"] per gate
  number_of_qubits: 2,
  target_unitary: "CNOT_FLIPPED"  // matches TARGET_LIBRARY key
}
```
> Note: Parameterized gate support (theta) is being added in Week 2. Until then, gates is a flat string[].
> IMPORTANT: The wire format key is `gates`, not `circuit`. The inventory doc was wrong on this point.

### Simulate Response (BE → FE): `SimulationResponseDTO`
```typescript
{
  "validation_mode": "truth_table",  // NOTE: bug — currently has trailing colon "validation_mode:" — fix in Week 1
  results: Array<{
    input: number[],
    expected: number[],
    actual: number[],
    match: boolean
  }>,
  all_match: boolean
}
```

