## Key Backend Files (know these before modifying anything)

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `app/controllers/simulate.py` | `simulate_unitaries()` — the main loop; runs both trial and target through Cirq |
| `app/services/circuit_builder.py` | `CircuitBuilder` — constructs Cirq circuits from gate dicts |
| `app/services/simulator.py` | `CircuitSimulator` — runs wavefunction simulation; `run_and_measure` path is UNUSED |
| `app/config/gates.py` | `CirqGateMapper.apply()` — maps gate name strings → Cirq operations |
| `app/config/target_library.py` | `TARGET_LIBRARY` — the ground truth for all levels |
| `app/services/target_builder.py` | `TargetUnitaryBuilder.build()` (active) + `get_unitary()` (legacy dead code — ignore) |
| `app/utils/helpers.py` | Pure functions: basis state generation, ket formatting, result extraction |
| `app/utils/qubit_orders.py` | Named qubit orders: Q0, Q1, C0_T1, C1_T0 |

## Key Frontend Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/App.tsx` | Root; wires all hooks; DndContext + DragOverlay |
| `src/hooks/useCircuit.ts` | `gates[]` state; addGate, removeGate, clearGates, setGateOrder |
| `src/hooks/useCircuitValidation.ts` | useMutation; handleCheck; builds and fires the API request |
| `src/hooks/useDragAndDrop.ts` | Maps tool IDs → Gate enum; onDragEnd → addGate |
| `src/controllers/simulate.ts` | `buildRequestFromLevel()` → UnitaryRequestDTO serialization |
| `src/config/levels.ts` | All level definitions + LEVEL_ORDER + getNextLevel() |
| `src/config/gates.ts` | allowedOrdersFor, labelFor, arityFor per gate |
| `src/components/GateDesign.tsx` | SVG glyphs — CNOTGlyph, CZGlyph, HGlyph, TGlyph, SGlyph, RXGlyph, RYGlyph, UGlyph |

